21/10/2008
SKOPJE, Macedonia -- Police have found a large cache of weapons and ammunition in an underground bunker in the village of Ljuboten, the interior ministry announced on Monday (October 20th).
Authorities seized 30 mortar shells -- apparently of Croatian origin -- one mortar and a considerable amount of ammunition, a statement said.
Police believe the weapons date from the 2001 conflict between Albanian rebels and Macedonian armed forces.
(MIA, Makfax, A1, Javno - 20/10/08)
